===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# The control center of the [[central nervous system]] of an [[animal]] located in the [[skull]] which is responsible for [[perception]], [[cognition]], [[attention]], [[memory]], [[emotion]], and [[action]].
# An [[intelligent]] person.
#: ''He was a total '''brain'''.''
# {{context|English pluralia tantum}} A person who provides the intelligence required for something.
#: ''The '''brains''' behind the scheme''
# (''in plural'' '''brains''') [[intellect|Intellect]].
#: ''He has a lot of '''brains'''.''
# By analogy with a human brain, the part of a [[machine]] or [[computer]] that performs [[calculation]]s.
#: ''The computer's '''brain''' is capable of millions of calculations a second.''

